arStrings.szText: A Necromancer pilgrim journeys to the holy city of Necropolis.
I met a traveling Necromancer pilgrim, Kyros, who encouraged me to visit the Gates of Necropolis once they had been liberated.
Travel to the Gates of Necropolis
I have once again encountered Kyros, the Necromancer pilgrim. I should speak with him about the possibility for work he mentioned earlier.
The Jeweled Finger of Ezra-Kan, first Gatekeeper of Necropolis, has been stolen. Kyros has asked me to find it, recommending I start my search at a nearby ruin.
Upon arriving at the shrine of Rathma, I have been unable to find the Jeweled Finger of Ezra-Kan. The only part of the shrine I have not searched is a stinking pit going deeper into the earth.
I have taken the Jeweled Finger of Ezra-Kan from among the half-living damned within the Pit of Anguish. I should return it to the Necromancer Kyros at the Gates of Necropolis.
I have discovered a wretched pit filled with rotting corpses. Perhaps the thief who stole the Jeweled Finger of Ezra-Kan from Necropolis festers among their number.
Search for clues in the Pit of Anguish
I met a traveling Necromancer pilgrim, Kyros, who encouraged me to visit the Gates of Necropolis once they had been liberated.
Enter the Festering Dark leading to Necropolis
